SIMPLE: forceps
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forceps
<hw>For"ceps</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>forceps</ets>, <ets>-cipis</ets>, from the root of
<ets>formus</ets> Hot + <ets>capere</ets> to take; akin to E.
<ets>heave</ets>. Cf. <er>Furnace</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A pair
of pinchers, or tongs; an instrument for grasping, holding firmly, or
exerting traction upon, bodies which it would be inconvenient or
impracticable to seize with the fingers, especially one for delicate
operations, as those of watchmakers, surgeons, accoucheurs, dentists,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The caudal forceps-shaped
appendage of earwigs and some other insects. See
<er>Earwig</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dressing forceps</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Dressing</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Force pump</ent>⟦br⟧
